<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9078&amp;p=96903#p96903"><![CDATA[
Isometric games were all the rage in Britain.  I quite like their look-- they pack in a lot of realistic detail into monochrome hi-res graphics.<br /><br />By the way, I actually translated (from a Japanese book) an interview  with the makers of Solstice II (Equinox) and put it on my page last week:  <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.chrismcovell.com/secret/sp_Solstice2int.html">http://www.chrismcovell.com/secret/sp_Solstice2int.html</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=355">ccovell</a> — Wed Jul 18, 2012 6:24 pm</p><hr />
